Will I be doing this for the rest of my life? Probably not. As of right now, when Iâ€™m having these â€œdownâ€ moments and thinking my life is a mess, writing this journal helps me put myself together.

lmk in the comments if you've tried this or youâ€™re going through the same struggle https://t.co/OgM5HYqGon

The best part about this journal is, it literally takes only 5 minutes. And itâ€™s probably the most effective thing I could ever do in 5 minutes. 

Name a better thing you can do in only 5 minutes.  Again, donâ€™t get me wrong, Iâ€™m not saying this def helps you, but it did help me.

You probably think this sounds like bs and tbh thatâ€™s exactly how I felt. After two days of writing, I felt less anxious and more motivated. Just a little bit, but it worked. 

I actually finished some work and just random chores Iâ€™ve been procrastinating for a long time.

Just like the quote says: â€œthis is not a magic pill, but thereâ€™s certainly some magic at work here. This journal is your guide.â€

This journal is for you if you never write journals, like me.

Shout out to my friend @ryanli_me  for giving me this journal. Iâ€™d be lying if I say it is a panacea and just makes everything right instantly, but I do feel more productive, positive, and motivated after writing for 2 weeks.
Just FYI Iâ€™m not getting paid and neither am I a psychiatrist. Just a dude who found this helpful personally and wanted to share.

Idk if this happens to any of you guys but I just get upset for no reason sometimes, not passionate about work, life, or anything, really. 

If you get this quite often and want to do something about it, Iâ€™d like to recommend this â€œ5-minute journalâ€ I been trying.

@wsdxbz1 Hey! This is Roy from CyberConnect. 

We do appreciate that you openly expressed your concerns and thank you for your feedback! 

Just wrote a thread to answer some of your questions and concerns. Feel free to stop by and check it out!

https://t.co/nBFcysPldu

12) Last but not least, if you donâ€™t mind, I'm more than happy to discuss your concerns & answer any questions you may have over a Twitter Space that everyone is welcome to join! 

We know how important it is to have more open conversations and show gratitude for early members
11) Again, we realize it may have neglected some new Web3 dwellers. Going forward, our focus will be on where we create value for EVERYONE on Web3 and how everyone can contribute:

10) I totally agree that all contributions should be recognized. Building connections and getting people involved in our protocol is effectively contributing to a system of holistic identities and user-centric web - a collective value creation of meaningful social experiences.

9) We also have the Xmas POAP for everyone who helps us spread the word on Twitter; a builder POAP for our hackathon participants, and we will have a special POAP to reward our â€œDoormanâ€ (mods) and contributors in our community.

8) All you have to do is to verify your Twitter on CyberConnect and have at least 5 followers on CyberConnect. And we paid for all the gas fees.  

We were trying hard to make sure everyone has a fair chance to get a piece of something, an NFT, a POAP, or a unique role on Discord

7) POAP is just one of the many methods we reward our early adopters and contributors. 

For the exact same campaign, more than 27k unique addresses with previous on-chain activities have minted the â€œVerified Web3 Dwellersâ€ NFT within two weeks.

6) The emphasis for theâ€œWeb3 Curatorâ€POAP is curation. Considering how early Web3 social is, we want to encourage users to discover early, follow and support Web3-native KOLs and projects, and spread the word for them. Then, the 10% early-movers and gem-seekers will get rewarded

5) Reputation matters, Web2 or not. With Web3 we make it better recognized and encourage people to accrue it from early on. 
Meanwhile, Web2 social will still be a significant part of our identity so it should be recognized and justly migrated to Web3 if you wish.

4) Gotta be honest upfront, we wanted the campaign to help bootstrap our early adoption, so we could onboard more partners and so more value for our users out of connections and reputation. KOLs are crucial for evangelizing crypto space in general and Web3.

3) On the contrary to â€œcontrolling your social activitiesâ€, we reclaim your social connection data which used to be locked in social platforms and give it back to you. You are solely responsible for how it grows and is used. 

Fact check.

2) First of all, thank you @wsdxbz1 for openly expressing your concerns! 

To get things clear, we are not a â€œWeb3 Twitterâ€. We're a social graph protocol - help everyone to have an identity that travels across all dApps, using the protocol standards to deliver better experiences

1) Yesterday, @wsdxbz1 has expressed some concerns over the #LetsCyberConnect event, especially the way we distribute the POAPs. 

Openness is everything and we appreciate it. 

As the head of community of CyberConnect, I feel like I should say something.
